author: The Road to Wembley (FA Cup Finals 1923 - 2000)
text:
Remembering the former #Bolton & #Arsenal player David Jack who was born OTD in 1898

He won the #FACup 3 times, with #BWFC in 1923 & 1926 and with #AFC in 1930

He scored the first ever goal at Wembley in 1923, he also scored in 1926

He died in 1958 aged 60

author: The Road to Wembley (FA Cup Finals 1923 - 2000)
text:
Remembering the late former #LeedsUnited & Wales goalkeeper Gary Sprake who was born OTD in 1945

Sprake played in two #FACup finals for #Leeds, in 1965 & 1970 losing on both occasions. 

He was injured for the ‚Äò70 replay.

He passed away in 2016 aged 71.
